<%- include("../partials/header") %>
<div class="flex flex-col items-center min-h-screen bg-white py-10">
  <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl shadow-lg p-8 w-full max-w-md">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3 text-green-800 text-center">Prime Checker</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-5 text-center">
      <span class="font-semibold text-green-700">Prime numbers</span> are natural numbers greater than 1 that have no divisors other than 1 and themselves. They are the building blocks of all numbers!
    </p>
    <form id="primeForm" class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <input type="number" id="primeInput" min="0" placeholder="Enter an integer" required class="w-full px-3 py-2 border rounded focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-green-400"/>
      <button type="submit" class="bg-green-700 hover:bg-green-800 transition text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded mt-2">
        Check
      </button>
    </form>
    <div id="primeResult" class="mt-6 text-xl text-blue-700 text-center"></div>
    <div class="mt-6">
      <div class="bg-green-100 border-l-4 border-green-600 p-3 rounded">
        <span class="font-medium text-green-800">Definition:</span>
        <span class="text-gray-800">A prime number is only divisible by <span class="font-mono">1</span> and itself.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-3 flex justify-center items-center gap-2">
        <span class="bg-blue-200 text-blue-900 px-3 py-1 rounded text-xs font-medium shadow">Example: 7 is prime (only divisible by 1 & 7)</span>
        <span class="bg-red-100 text-red-800 px-3 py-1 rounded text-xs font-medium shadow">Example: 9 is not prime (divisible by 1, 3, and 9)</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-4 text-gray-500 text-xs text-center italic">
      Explore patterns in primes and why they're crucial in cryptography!
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<script src="/public/js/script.js"></script>
